author: @decodingdatascience
text: üéØ Key Takeaways for quick navigation:  00:00 üìä Projects play a significant role in landing data analytics jobs, according to 75% of data enthusiasts surveyed. 01:11 üìà Building projects that solve real-world problems showcases self-motivation and can impress employers. 03:04 üöÄ Providing a concise summary (TLDR) of your project's highlights is essential for making your portfolio stand out to potential employers. 04:00 üìù Using a unique and personally meaningful dataset in your project can make it more impactful and interesting. 08:00 ü•ë Going above and beyond by sharing clean datasets, providing code references, and creating a website to showcase your project can make it stand out as a model project  Follow us for more generative AI videos @decodingdatascience

author: @AestheticVibesMusic
text: I'm from Ukraine and I've landed my first job as a Data Analyst that will be starting Monday. It took me 50-100 replies, 5 interviews, and the interview for my job was the easiest with the most minor questions. I have no moderate projects like those showcased in the video, but I've put my SQL coursework I did 2 years ago on github, made little PowerBI project. I have bachelor's degree in Software Engineering, no certificates and during the interview we've talked about project idea I've never done using Python, YouTube API, pandas, matplotlib. The job required creative person and Head of Department liked me for my ideas and  knowledge.  The job itself involves 30% Data Engineering transforming data from 1C to a Date Warehouse, and 70% Data Analytics using SQL, PowerBI. Good luck to everyone struggling to get a job ü§û
